# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We simply traverse the matrix column wise, when we encounter that two consecutive elements of the column are not in lexicographic order, we add the column number in a temporary list `c`.
After Traversing the whole list of strings, there's a high chance of having redundant values in the list `c`. Thus , we typecaste the list `c` to a set, which will drop any redundant values in the list and have distinct column numbers to be deleted. At the end we will simply return the length of the set `c`.


# Code
```
class Solution:
    def minDeletionSize(self, strs: List[str]) -> int:
        c = []
        for i in range(len(strs)-1):
            for j in range(len(strs[0])):
                if strs[i][j] > strs[i+1][j]:
                    c.append(j)
        return len(set(c))
```

