# Approach
1. Traverse all strings column by column
2. Compare $$col$$th character of $$row$$th string with  $$col$$th character of $$row-1$$th string and increase $$ans$$ by $$1$$ if first character is lexographically greater than latter character
# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n*m)$$ , where n is the number of strings in array and m is the length of each string 

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$(Integer variables: n , len , ans , row , col)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minDeletionSize(vector<string>& strs) 
    {
        int n=strs.size() , len=strs[0].length() , ans=0;

        for(int col=0;col<len;col++)
        {
            for(int row=1;row<n;row++)
            {
                if(strs[row-1][col]>strs[row][col]) //Column is unsorted 
                {
                    ans++;
                    break; //no need to check further in column
                }
            }
        }    
        return ans;
    }
};
```

