# Intuition
We need to do columnwise matrix traversal .

# Approach
1. We must check whether the no.of rows == 1 beforehand to avoid unnecessary computation of strings because if there is only one row in the matrix it cannot be compared with another string of the same column and therefore the matrix will always remain sorted columnwise.  For Example strs = ["abc"] or ["a"] .
2.  We must use outer loop for traversing in columnwise manner among the strings .
3.   We must use the inner loop for traversing rows in the matrix or strings in the array according to a particular column or index respectively and check whether they are in lexicographical order or not . See the implementation attached below .

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N * K)
where 
N = length of the array of strings "strs" ,
K = length of each string . 

- Space complexity:
O(1)
As only an extra variable unsorted_columns is required .
# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int minDeletionSize(String[] strs) {
        if(strs.length == 1)
            return 0;
        int unsorted_columns = 0;
        for(int i = 0 ; i < strs[0].length() ; ++i)
        {
            for(int j = 0 ; j < (strs.length - 1) ; ++j)
            {
                if(strs[j].charAt(i) > strs[j+1].charAt(i))
                {
                    ++unsorted_columns;
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
        return unsorted_columns;
    }
}
```

